'''Gregor Fu<U+010D>ka''' ({{IPA-it|<U+02C8>fut<U+0283>ka}}; born 7 August 1971 in [[Kranj]], [[Slovenia]], [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia|SFR Yugoslavia]]) is an [[Italy|Italian]] [[basketball]] player of [[Slovenia]]n origin. A 215&nbsp;cm (7'1") [[forward-center]], he was a [[Mister Europa Player of the Year]] and a [[Euroscar Award|Euroscar Player of the Year]] laureate in 2000.

== Pro career ==
He has played with [[KK Union Olimpija|Olimpija Ljubljana]] in Slovenia during the 1989-90 season, then he moved to Italy, playing for [[Pallacanestro Trieste|Stefanel Trieste]] (1990-1994), [[Olimpia Milano|Stefanel Milano]] (1994-1997) and [[Fortitudo Bologna|Teamsystem Bologna a.k.a. Paf Bologna a.k.a. Skipper Bologna]] (1997-2002). Then he played in Spain with [[FC Barcelona Basquet|FC Barcelona]] (2003-2006) and with [[Akasvayu Girona]] (2006-07). He then came back to Italy in the 2007-08 season, playing with [[Lottomatica Virtus Roma]].

== Titles and awards ==
Fu<U+010D>ka has won numerous tournaments, including the 1996 [[Serie A (basketball)|Italian Championship]] and the 1996 [[Coppa Italia di pallacanestro maschile|Italian Cup]] with [[Olimpia Milano|Stefanel Milano]], and the 2000 Italian Championship, the 1998 Italian Cup and the 1998 [[Supercoppa Italiana di Pallacanestro Maschile|Italian Super Cup]] with [[Fortitudo Bologna]]. 

In the year 2003 with [[FC Barcelona Basquet|FC Barcelona]], he won the [[Asociaci<U+00F3>n de Clubs de Baloncesto|Spanish ACB League]], the [[Copa del Rey de Baloncesto|Spanish King's Cup]], and the [[Euroleague]] (thus winning the [[Triple Crown in Basketball]]). In 2004, he again won the Spanish ACB League with Barcelona and he also won the [[Supercopa de Espa<U+00F1>a de Baloncesto|Spanish Super Cup]] with Barcelona in 2004.

He also played in the [[Kora<U+0107> Cup]] final in 1995 and 1996 with [[Olimpia Milano|Stefanel Milano]]. In 2000, Fu<U+010D>ka was named the 2000 Italian League Finals [[MVP]]. In 2001, he earned the Italian League All-Star Game MVP trophy.

== Italian national team ==
Fu<U+010D>ka played with Italy's junior national team at the 1991 [[FIBA Under-19 World Championship]], where he won the silver medal. He also played at the [[FIBA Under-21 World Championship]] with Italy's junior national team in 1993.

With the senior [[Italy national basketball team|Italian national basketball team]], Fu<U+010D>ka played at the [[Basketball at the 2000 Summer Olympics|2000 Olympic Basketball Tournament]] and he won the gold medal at the [[Eurobasket 1999|1999 European Championship]], where he was named the tournament's [[MVP]]. Fu<U+010D>ka also won a silver medal at the [[Eurobasket 1997|1997 European Championship]]. He also played at the [[1998 FIBA World Championship]], and at the [[Eurobasket 1995|1995 European Championship]] and the [[Eurobasket 2001|2001 European Championship]].

